# Wish list.
#
# Effort tags: XS = a few lines / one-shot · S = small, one layer · M = a
# session, multiple layers · L = full feature (DB+API+realtime+UI) · XL = major
# project / new security model. Backlog is sorted by effort, lowest first.
# "→" marks a decision worth making before the work starts.

## Done

- Hide disabled users from the roster ordinary users see (admins still see them).
- Drop the member button/list in DMs.
- Refresh display name / avatar when they change (live, no refresh).
- Let members leave a private channel; mods+ may remove others.
- In DMs, either participant may pin/unpin.
- Semver + About dialog. Version constant (config.Version), surfaced via
  /api/instance and an About modal opened from the sidebar brand.
- Durable notifications + opt-in desktop notifications (earlier work).
- Mute channels/DMs (durable, cross-device; full silence) — v0.9.1.
- Suppress historical "deleted" tombstones; only live-session deletes tombstone — v0.9.2.
- Update-available banner via a WS hello{version} handshake — v0.9.3.
- Admin stats panel (user/channel/message counts + live connections) — v1.0.0.
- Autocomplete for @-pings (username + display name, channel-scoped, keyboard nav) — v1.0.4.
- Mobile swipe gestures (right = sidebar, left = members; horizontal vs. scroll disambiguated) — v1.0.5.
- Idle status (10-min timer, hidden-tab accelerated; ephemeral hub flag, amber dot same as away) — v1.0.6.
- Typing indicators (throttled WS frames, server-side 5 s TTL, channel-scoped relay, "X is typing…" above composer) — v1.0.7.
- Every message timestamp links to that point in history (window-around-id store
  query, #c<id>/m<id> hash, load+scroll+highlight, "viewing history" banner) —
  v1.0.8; v1.0.9 polish: canonical permalink hash helper (fixed a /m/ vs /m drift
  that broke shared links on fresh load) + feedback when an anchor is deleted/gone;
  v1.0.10: bidirectional history paging (after= cursor → scroll *down* loads newer)
  and the "viewing history" banner only shows when the window has a gap to the tail;
  v1.0.11: forward paging now holds scroll position instead of snapping to the
  bottom (the snap stranded mobile readers at the end so the next page never
  loaded), and prefetches ~a screen early so reading downward stays seamless;
  v1.0.12: scroll loading is now driven by IntersectionObserver sentinels (the
  scrollTop math never fired reliably on mobile), and a jump probes forward once
  so brief conversations fill the cut-off tail and never show a spurious banner.
- Message search (full-text, scoped to accessible channels) — v1.0.17. Postgres
  to_tsvector('english') + GIN functional index (migration 0007); websearch_to_tsquery
  tolerates arbitrary input. GET /api/search?q=&before=&limit= scopes to the caller's
  accessible channels (accessibleChannelIDs, same rule as canAccessChannel — DMs stay
  members-only even for mods), newest-first with keyset pagination. Header 🔍 opens a
  debounced search modal; clicking a hit reuses jumpToMessage. Renders via the
  escape-first formatMessage (no ts_headline, preserving the XSS invariant).

## Backlog (sorted by effort)

4. [L] Custom emojis.
   Storage (a bytes-blob table + shortcode, like avatars), upload/manage endpoints
   (admin?), and :shortcode: rendering in format.js that PRESERVES its escape-first
   XSS invariant. A picker is the nice-to-have.

5. [L] Reactions.
   reactions(message_id, user_id, emoji) + add/remove endpoints + realtime
   reaction.add/remove + aggregation into the message payload/state + UI. Touches
   every layer. Pairs naturally with #4.

6. [XL] OTR / end-to-end encrypted messaging.
   The big one and a different security model: client-side crypto, key
   generation/exchange, key + trust management (and multi-device), server storing
   only ciphertext, verification UI. Signal/OMEMO class — wants its own design pass.

## Meta / future ideas (not yet scoped)

- Let's broaden the pinned messages modal on desktop, it's a little bit horizontally cramped.

- Mods+ should be able to update channel topics

- Messages should render linked images inline. Messages consisting of just a link to an image should hide the URL and only render that image. (I don't have interest in running a CDN at this time, but this will allow memes and gifs.)

- Links should render [text](url). Bonus points: pasting a URL onto selected text automatically formats it this way.

- Edit box should be inline rather than cheap-feeling popup

- A Claude agent running on this box, wired into the chat, so work requests can
  be sent from inside Rivendell itself (chat → agent → commits/deploys). Its own
  design pass: how it authenticates, which channel/DM it listens on, how it
  reports progress back, and the safety rails around what it's allowed to run.
